* BrightBlade looked up at Perndabot as his eyes slid down her form, she
sighed, shook her head and grinned.*

" See anything you like?"

* She snickered as she then turned her attention back towards her task at
hand, then thinking that it was about time that she reported back to base so
that they would know that there would be some in coming information on the
new Maximal base.
BrightBlade made sure that Gangon wouldn't slip from her grasp, then tapped
her com-link. The coded Predacon frequency.*

" Predacon base, this is BrightBlade. I'm currently 20 clicks from the
Cybertronien Fire. Expect a particularly large amount of vital data to be
loaded directly into the main console from the Maximal main data base. I'll
be back with the loaded cross section of their ship in a mega-cycle or so.
If it's possible I want at least two bots processing the data that comes in.
I'm not infiltrating the enemy base just to use the bathrooms."

* She looked down at Gangon's spark.*

" There should be diagnostics and diagrams of security programs, weapons and
so on in the incoming data. It'll take a bit of program memory so it might
be smart to begin making room for the data now before I get in and transfer
it to you. Oh, and Rampage? If Lord Hell Beast isn't there it would be nice
if you took the position of commander until I returned. That's all. My next
report will be when I'm ready to transfer the data. BrightBlade out."

* The deactivating her com-link she looked back at Perndabot, a smile on her
face. If she knew one thing that it was that she could trust her fellow
Predacons, feeling that they were more a part of her then ever when she had
become second in command.
She liked the idea of all of those talented bot's behind her, liking the
responsibility it gave.
She was going to get all this data for them, so that THEY could win this
war. Putting her life on the line for them, to get this data so that the
Maximals would soon fall!*
